metadata.name: Phantom Voids: An algorithm study #24
metadata.description:
This is the first series of my algorithmic studies. This study is an exploration of algorithms  to create an abstract artwork using only lines. Multiple color palettes with high color contrast have been used. It takes a short time to complete.

Open it in the live mode, it will be saved automatically after completion.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Bound #7
metadata.description:
Our journey consists of events that happen one after the other, and most of the time these are quite linear. The parts we remember and cherish often happen when we change paths. "Bound" is about letting go and being open to events that are unpredictable and thus gaining new colorfull experiences. 

This collection exists of connected rectangles on a tight grid with lines cutting their way through the patterns made with a simple algorithm.

Press s in live mode to download.

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje November 2022

metadata.name: Provence #288
metadata.description:
The south of France namely the Provence has a cultural history of being an inspiration for impressionists and post-impressionists in the past.
For me personally the Provence is the place i was spending long, peaceful holidays as a child within beautiful nature.
This work does not so much aim for being realistic, rather than give an impression or feeling for this wonderful landscape. 
There are just a few different elements and concepts and yet there is variety of fascinating results.
I really hope you will enjoy your minting.

Notes:
STARTUP AND RENDERING MAY TAKE SOME TIME. (Up to 1min)
Code was written in typescript.
The only used libraries were chroma.js and simplex-noise

metadata.name: Lucid Dream #264
metadata.description:
Lucid Dream is our contribution to celebrate #fxhashturnsone!

 It’s our first long-form collection with shaders! Throughout the year we had the opportunity to explore and improve ourselves. Therefore, we wanted to celebrate this anniversary with a technique/medium that is new to us.

You can explore hidden textures and colors by interacting the animation with your cursor.

“Lucid dreaming is the experience of achieving conscious awareness of dreaming while still asleep. Lucid dreams are generally thought to arise from non-lucid dreams in REM sleep (Stephen LaBerge, 1986).“

----Best experienced in full screen----

Probabilities;

- Unique preview features (exclusive for preview image)

- Generative color palette

- 2 different light styles

- 4 different interaction animation styles 

- Some unique features

This piece is using shaders thus results may be different from device to device.

You can press 's' in liveMode to save the current state as .png.

Half of the primary sales go to the Processing Foundation.

Made with p5js and openGL shaders.
@distcollective, November 2022

metadata.name: fx(mandala) #244
metadata.description:
Outer mandalas represent the universe or world-system and are traditionally offered as thank you gifts. In this case it’s my offering to the fxhash community as a celebration of #fxhashturnsone. 

SOME MINTS WILL BE GOLDEN TICKETS
A golden ticket AND the iteration directly before it will each receive a free 8 x 10in special edition signed physical made from 12 layers of laser cut museum board. 

Physicals for all mints can be requested and/or claimed at https://alleditions.art

Outer Mandalas is part of a broader series I am working on that explores the use of techniques and patterns from sacred geometries using generative randomness. I use generative algorithms to create “blueprints” that can be transferred out of the physical realm and into the real world as multi-layered three dimensional sculptures. 

I create limited edition physical “prints” for Outer Mandalas by using a high powered laser to precisely cut through 4-ply museum boards (the same stuff you frame a picture with) to create 12 unique layers. I then stack and carefully glue each layer together in order to create a dynamic relief that plays with light and shadow. These pieces are visually engaging artworks that tend to spark conversation whenever they are seen.  

A big thank you to the fxhash platform team and all the passionate collectors and generative artists I’ve met over the past year. It’s been my honor to be a part of this amazing community. 

s to save as a layered SVG 
p to save as a PNG
e to explode the layers
Click and drag the mouse to change the shadows. 

This generative is VERY intensive and probably won’t render very well on a mobile device.

metadata.name: Color Clouds #49
metadata.description:
Color Clouds was created to celebrate #fxhashturnsone - the one year anniversary of fxhash and is a result of experimenting with multi-layered flow-field visualisations in p5.js.

50% of all revenue including royalties will be donated to the Processing Foundation.


In Live-View or when iframe is focused...
...hit 's' to save the current frame
...hit 'x' to reset the rendering
...hit 'r' to toggle a square aspect-ratio


---URL-Parameters---

[&speed] = default is 100; set to any natural number
[&square] = default is 1; set to 0 for responsive viewport rendering
[&density] = default is 2; set to any natural number to set a custom pixel density

Created with p5.js using map2 and post5.

- @TeNinEightNFTs

metadata.name: Tilemoji #169
metadata.description:
This collection of low resolution generative art is presented using emojis rather than an image, so it can be copied like normal text. You are also welcome to take a screenshot for sharing or printing. Most results are designed to fit in a 280 character tweet, except for rare extra large variants. There are five different generative algorithms possible, each with their own set of parameters. Emojis are rendered using the Twemoji font and may look different in some environments.

Thank you for supporting my work during the first year of fxhash. For me it has been a life changing experience. I am forever grateful for all of the art and friendships we've created. Many of us have met on social media, so I developed this special project with a fun way to display and share. Congrats to artists, collectors, and developers for an amazing year!

This work is part of the fxhash anniversary event (#fxhashturnsone)
All of primary sale proceeds will go to Save Pakistan

Code and Outputs are Copyright 2022 Frank Force

metadata.name: Schetsboek (reissue) #141
metadata.description:
This is my little tribute to fx (hash and fam).

During an important phone call, I was put on hold. Unconsciously, I began to scribble in my sketchbook. Research shows that scribbling helps focusing, but I dreamed away nonetheless until my pages were filled with scribbles, notes, shopping and a to-do list. 

Mint a uniquely generated page from my non-existent 100% coded sketchbook (except text typography). 

The page may contain many scribbles and drawings in pen, felt-tip pen, pencil, or less: often references to artists I admire, some in the form of loose scribbles, others in the form of riddles. Those drawings are drawn with code and vary. Unfortunately, I wasn’t able to incorporate tributes to all art and every artist I admire. The sketchbook would never finish. Thanks to rudxane I know that it’s ok to publish something unfinished ;-). 

One reference that appears in every token is to Sol Lewitt, an incredible source of inspiration. His artworks consist of instructions. Your sketch book pages contain instructions too. You will find the instructions for the artwork scribbled on your unique page by pressing i.

Curious how the work would look without the ‘distracting’ scribbles and coffee stains? Press ‘a’, ‘w’, or ‘g’. 

800 x 800 px

Press ‘s’ to save an image.

Made with p5js and the amazing p5.scribble.js library by Janneck Wullschleger.

Font used: Sacremento-Regular under the SIL Open Font License (OFL).

See license.md for the licenses of both.

Thank you all!

metadata.name: warpGrid #64
metadata.description:
warpGrid uses noise fields to subdivide, warp, and color a plane. For each iteration, separate noise fields are used to perform each action. 

Variable features include: canvas framing, background, 11 different color palettes, grid size, cell shape and fit within grid, edge style, and texture. 

Note: some rarer textures take longer to render.

Type "s" to save the image.

metadata.description: gridography is an ink-dot inspired collection, with randomly generated features such as grid density, distortion angle, and distortion amount. metadata.name: YouAreAMazing1.0 #158
metadata.description:
YouAreAMazing1.0 

 Playable, colorful, and often *very challenging* generative-art mazes.
   
 Each maze begins with an "intro" animation of its genesis when opened.
   
 Mazes range in size from from "normal" to "MASSIVE".
   They're made of colorful interconnected rooms.
   Some mazes are spacious, others are downright claustrophobic.
   Floors are colored using 1 of 16 palettes of varying rarities.
   
   Some mazes feature a cat.
   
   Each twist and turn of every maze is randomly chosen,
     so there are BILLIONS of possible mazes.
   
   
   
   ... oh yeah, they're also playable ...
   
   keyboard:
   wasd keys navigate
   'h' peeks (cheats)
   
   touchscreen:
   touch edges to navigate
   top-right corner to peek (cheat)
   
   
   To PRINT your maze, press 'p'
   This will temporarily display the maze & its features in monochrome
     and open the 'print' dialog.
   
   When you complete your maze, you may save a file
     to remind people that "amazing you are"!
